          INTRODUCTION

          THE TIME SHARING SUBSYSTEM OPTION (TSSO) IS A PACKAGE DESIGNED
          INCREASE  OPERATIONS  AND END USER PRODUCTIVITY BY PROVIDING T
          LIKE SERVICES TO THE MVS OPERATOR, AND MVS  CONSOLE  SERVICES
          THE TSO AND NCCF USER. TSSO CAN GREATLY ENHANCE AN INSTALLATIO
          EFFORTS TO EFFICIENTLY CONTROL AND OPERATE MVS BY AUTOMATING M
          OPERATIONAL  PROCEDURES.   THIS DOCUMENT DESCRIBES THE CHANGES
          TSSO IN VERSION 4, RELEASE  3.  KNOWLEDGE  OF  TSSO  CONCEPTS
          ASSUMED.1

          VERSION  4.3  OF  THE  TIME  SHARING  SUBSYSTEM  OPTION  PROVI
          ENHANCEMENTS  OVER  THE PREVIOUS RELEASE IN FIVE MAIN AREAS. T
          ARE:

            1.  ENHANCEMENTS  TO  THE  OPERATIONS   PRODUCTIVITY   FACIL
                (TSSO/OPF). THESE ENHANCEMENTS ARE SPECIFICALLY IN THE A
                OF INCREASED AUTOMATION CAPABILITY THROUGH  EXPANDED  CL
                ORIENTED  TSSO COMMANDS, AND THE REMOVAL OF THE RESTRICT
                OF ONLY ONE OUTSTANDING OSCMD IN THE SYSTEM.

            2.  ENHANCEMENTS   TO   THE   AUTOMATED   OPERATIONS   FACIL
                (TSSO/AOF). THESE ENHANCEMENTS PROVIDE EASE OF USE FEATU
                FOR SYSTEM  PROGRAMMERS  AND  OPERATORS  DEALING  WITH
                TSSO/AOF COMPONENT.

            3.  THE ADDITION OF AN INTERFACE TO THE NETWORK  COMMUNICATI
                CONTROL  FACILITY (NCCF). THIS INTERFACE ALLOWS THE NETW
                OPERATOR TO ISSUE MVS, JES2 OR  OTHER  SUBSYSTEM  COMMAN
                AND RETRIEVE THE RESPONSE AT THE NCCF TERMINAL.

            4.  THE TSSO CONSOLE SECURITY FEATURE HAS BEEN UPGRADED TO
                THE  SYSTEM  ACCESS  FACILITY FOR ITS INTERFACE TO SECUR
                SYSTEMS.




