          ENHANCEMENTS TO THE OPERATOR PRODUCTIVITY FACILITY

          THE FOLLOWING ENHANCEMENTS WERE MADE TO THE OPERATOR PRODUCTIV
          FACILITY:

            1.  TSSO NOW ALLOWS MORE THAN ONE SIMULTANEOUS  CALLER  OF
                OSCMD  TSO  COMMAND. THE INSTALLATION DEFINES THE NUMBER
                SIMULTANEOUS CALLERS IN THE NEW NUMCONS  PARAMETER  IN
                TSSO  INITIALIZATION  DECK.  INSTALLATIONS  MUST DEFINE
                SUBSYSTEM CONSOLE TO MVS FOR EVERY SIMULTANEOUS  CALLER
                OSCMD.  IN ADDITION, AN INSTALLATION MAY CHOOSE TO DEDIC
                ONE SUBSYSTEM CONSOLE FOR THE TSSO ADDRESS SPACE.  THIS
                ACCOMPLISHED  THROUGH  A  DEDICATE PARAMETER ON THE NUMC
                STATEMENT. TSSO 4.3 PROVIDES AN EXPANDED  OPERATOR  COMM
                (#.Q SCON) TO MONITOR THE STATUS OF THE SUBSYSTEM CONSOL
                THIS WILL ALLOW AN INSTALLATION TO DETERMINE WHO  IS  US
                THE SUBSYSTEM CONSOLES, AND HOW MANY ARE NEEDED.

            2.  THE OSCMD COMMAND HAS BEEN REWRITTEN FOR TSSO 4.3.  IT
                SUPPORTS  THE  CAPABILITY  TO  DIRECT  THE  RESPONSE  OF
                OPERATING SYSTEM, JES2 OR SUBSYSTEM COMMAND TO

                  1.  A TSO TERMINAL - IF  OSCMD  WAS  ISSUED  FROM  A
                      ADDRESS SPACE.

                  2.  THE MVS CONSOLE -  IF  OSCMD  WAS  PART  OF  A  CL
                      INITIATED FROM THE TSSO ADDRESS SPACE.

                  3.  CLIST VARIABLES - IF OSCMD WAS ISSUED FROM A CLIST

                THE REDIRECTION  OF  MVS  COMMAND  OUTPUT  IS  ACCOMPLIS
                THROUGH  A CLIST VARIABLE (CMDRESP), WHICH IS USED AS IN
                TO OSCMD.

                OSCMD NOW SUPPORTS A USER EXIT, TO ALLOW AN INSTALLATION
                CODE  A  ROUTINE  TO  DETERMINE THE MVS COMMAND GROUP LE
                (E.G. SYSTEM, I/O, MASTER OR INFO) THE TSO USER IS  ALLO
                TO  ISSUE.  THE  DEFAULT  VERSION OF THE OSCMDATH USER E
                ALLOWS THE TSO USER THE AUTHORITY  OF  AN  MVS  INFORMAT
                ONLY  CONSOLE,  UNLESS  THE X'C0' BITS ARE TURNED ON IN
                USERDATA FIELD OF THE TSO USER'S UADS ENTRY.  THIS  MAY
                DONE   THROUGH   THE   USERDATA  PARAMETER  OF  THE  CHA
                SUBCOMMAND IN TSO ACCOUNT.













