            3.  A NEW COMMAND, OSWAIT, IS INCLUDED IN TSSO 4.3.  OSWAIT
                INTENDED  TO  BE  ISSUED  FROM  THE  CLIST ENVIRONMENT,
                ALLOWS THE CLIST TO WAIT FOR A SPECIFIED MESSAGE TO  APP
                ON  THE MVS CONSOLE. THE MESSAGE IS DEFINED IN THE TSSO/
                TABLE. FOR EXAMPLE, THE FOLLOWING CLIST WILL START  A  J
                WAIT FOR THE JOB TO COMPLETE, AND PURGE THE JOB.

                     PROC 0
                     /***************************************/
                     /* THIS CLIST WILL START A JOB, WAIT   */
                     /* FOR ITS COMPLETION, AND PURGE THE   */
                     /* JOB.                                */
                     /***************************************/

                     OSCMD S MYJOB
                     OSWAIT ENTRY(MYJOBEND)   TIMEOUT(60)
                     OSWTO MYJOB HAS ENDED...
                     OSCMD $P'MYJOB'
                     EXIT

                NOTE THAT THE TIMEOUT PARAMETER ALLOWS THE CLIST  DEVELO
                TO  SPECIFY  HOW  MANY  SECONDS  TO WAIT FOR THE MESSAGE
                APPEAR.  THE  FOLLOWING  TSSO/AOF  TABLE  DEFINITION  EN
                SUPPORTS  THE ABOVE CLIST (NOTE THAT IEF404I IS THE MVS
                ENDED MESSAGE).

                   TABENTRY MSG=IEF404I,ACTION=POST,TEST=((W,2,5,'MYJOB'


                THE OSWAIT  COMMAND  PROVIDES  FOR  SIGNIFICANT  AUTOMAT
                OPPORTUNITIES  THAT WERE (IN PREVIOUS VERSIONS OF TSSO)
                CUMBERSOME TO JUSTIFY DEVELOPMENT.

                OSWAIT DOES NOT NEED TO RUN FROM THE TSSO ADDRESS SPACE.
                THEORY,   AN  INSTALLATION  MAY  HAVE  MANY  OSWAIT  EVE
                OUTSTANDING AT ANY ONE TIME,  IN  DIFFERENT  TSO  OR  BA
                ADDRESS  SPACES. FOR EXAMPLE, A SIMPLE JOB SCHEDULER CAN
                CODED AS A CLIST USING THE  OSWAIT  AND  OSCMD  FACILITI
                THIS  CLIST CAN THEN BE RUN UNDER CONTROL OF A BATCH TMP
                A SEPARATE ADDRESS SPACE.

                IT SHOULD BE NOTED THAT ALTHOUGH TSSO  DOES  NOT  HAVE
                FACILITY  FOR  TIMER  DEPENDENT  COMMANDS,  IT  MAY UTIL
                EITHER THE JES2 AUTOMATIC COMMAND  FACILITY,  OR  THE  N
                "AT"  AND  "EVERY"  COMMANDS  TO  START  CLISTS AT SPECI
                TIMES, OR AT SPECIFIED INTERVALS.















