          ENHANCEMENTS TO THE AUTOMATED OPERATIONS FACILITY

          THE FOLLOWING ENHANCEMENTS WERE MADE TO THE AUTOMATED  OPERATI
          FACILITY (AOF) COMPONENT OF TSSO.

            1.  TSSO 4.3 SUPPORTS A  LABEL  ON  THE  TABENTRY  MACRO.  T
                PARAMETER  ALLOWS THE CODER OF THE AOF TABLE TO ASSOCIAT
                1-8 CHARACTER IDENTIFIER WITH  EACH  TABENTRY  MACRO.  T
                IDENTIFIER  CAN  THE BE USED AS A PARAMETER TO THE DISPA
                ALTAOF OR OSWAIT COMMANDS.

            2.  THE DISPAOF COMMAND IS ENHANCED TO DISPLAY  THE  NEW  LA
                ASSOCIATED  WITH  THE TABENTRY MACRO.  IT CAN ALSO USE T
                LABEL AS AN OPERAND TO THE ENTRYID PARAMETER.  DISPAOF W
                DISPLAY  ALL  ENTRIES  THAT  START  WITH  THE  GIVEN  EN
                IDENTIFIER. IN ADDITION, THE MSG PARAMETER OF  THE  DISP
                COMMAND  IS ENHANCED TO DISPLAY ALL ENTRIES THAT START W
                THE GIVEN MESSAGE IDENTIFIER, INSTEAD OF THE REQUIREMENT
                AN EXACT MATCH. FOR EXAMPLE, THE COMMAND

                   DISPAOF ENTRY(VTAMUP)


                WILL DISPLAY ALL TSSO/AOF TABLE  ENTRIES  THAT  HAVE  EN
                IDENTIFIER STARTING WITH "VTAMUP". THE COMMAND


                   DISPAOF MSG($HASP)


                WILL DISPLAY ALL TSSO/AOF TABLE ENTRIES WITH A  MESSAGE
                STARTING WITH $HASP (E.G. ALL JES2 RELATED ENTRIES).

            3.  A NEW CLIST (ASMTAB) IS PROVIDED TO ASSEMBLE AND  LINK-E
                THE  TSSO AOF TABLE. THIS CLIST REDUCES THE CUMBERSOME T
                OF PLACING A NEW AOF TABLE INTO PRODUCTION. IT IS  INTEN
                AS  AN  EXAMPLE,  AND WILL PROBABLY HAVE TO BE MODIFIED
                USE  IN  YOUR  INSTALLATION.   THE  CLIST  CAN  ASSEMBLE
                MODERATELY  SIZED TABLE, LINK EDIT THE RESULT, AND COPY
                RESULTING  LOAD  MODULE  INTO  SYS1.TSSOLOAD  IN  ABOUT
                SECONDS.   THE  CLIST  HAS  A RELOAD PARAMETER TO ISSUE
                TSSO #.RELOAD COMMAND UPON SUCCESSFUL  ASSEMBLY  AND  LI
                EDIT.

            4.  TSSO/AOF SUPPORTS THE OSWAIT  COMMAND  BY  RECOGNIZING
                SPECIFICATION OF ACTION=POST ON THE TABENTRY MACRO.















