          ADDITION OF AN INTERFACE TO NCCF

          THE NETWORK COMMUNICATION CONTROL  FACILITY  IS  AN  IBM  PROG
          PRODUCT THAT PROVIDES FOR NETWORK CONTROL IN ACF/VTAM OR ACF/T
          ENVIRONMENTS. THROUGH THE ADDITION OF AN OSCMD COMMAND PROCESS
          NCCF  NOW  SUPPORTS  CONTROL  OF  MVS,  JES2 OR OTHER SUBSYSTE
          SPECIFICALLY, THE NCCF VERSION OF OSCMD ALLOWS A NETWORK OPERA
          TO  ISSUE MVS, JES2 OR SUBSYSTEM COMMANDS, AND RETRIEVE RESPON
          AT THE NCCF TERMINAL.  THE NCCF VERSION OF OSCMD IS A  COMPLET
          SEPARATE ENTITY FROM THE TSO VERSION. THIS COMMAND PROCESSOR U
          STANDARD NCCF AND TSSO FACILITIES TO ALLOW AN  NCCF  OPERATOR
          ISSUE  OPERATING  SYSTEM  COMMANDS  AND  RETRIEVE  RESPONSES.
          COMMAND INSTALLS DIRECTLY  INTO  THE  NCCF  LOAD  LIBRARY,  OR
          CONCATENATED DATASET, AND IS DEFINED TO NCCF IN THE DSICMD MEM
          OF THE NCCF PARAMETER DATA SET.

          IT IS IMPORTANT TO NOTE THAT FOLLOWING POINTS:

            A.  THE NCCF AND TSO VERSIONS OF OSCMD SHARE THE SAME  POOL
                SUBSYSTEM CONSOLES. WHEN DEFINING THE NUMCONS PARAMETER,
                IS IMPORTANT TO CONSIDER THE NUMBER  OF  SIMULTANEOUS  N
                USERS THAT WILL BE USING TSSO FACILITIES.

            B.  NCCF DOES NOT REQUIRE APF  AUTHORIZATION  BECAUSE  OF  T
                FACILITY.  THIS  IS DESPITE THE FACT THAT OSCMD DOES IND
                RUN WITH APF AUTHORIZATION. TSSO GRANTS  APF  AUTHORIZAT
                TO  THE  NCCF VERSION OF OSCMD THROUGH THE USE OF MVS CR
                MEMORY SERVICES. TSSO PROVIDES A NEW OPERATOR COMMAND  (
                XMEM) TO MONITOR THE CROSS MEMORY ENVIRONMENT, AS WELL A
                DEBUG OPTION TO DISPLAY WHEN THE NCCF VERSION OF OSCMD
                CALLED THE TSSO CROSS MEMORY SERVICES ROUTINE.

                THIS AUTHORIZATION METHOD IS  CONTRASTED  WITH  IBM'S  O
                PRODUCT,  WHICH  REQUIRES  ALL DATASETS IN THE NCCF STEP
                CONCATENATION TO BE IN THE APF AUTHORIZATION LIST.

            C.  TSSO ASSUMES THAT ALL NCCF USERS ARE  AUTHORIZED  TO  IS
                MVS  MASTER CONSOLE COMMANDS. A USER EXIT IS PROVIDED IF
                INSTALLATION WISHES TO ALTER  THIS  DEFAULT.  THE  EXIT
                PASSED THE NCCF USER IDENTIFIER.

            D.  THE TSSO/NCCF OSCMD FACILITY FULLY SUPPORTS THE USE OF
                NCCF  ROUTE  COMMAND.  THIS ALLOWS REMOTE OPERATOR TO RO
                MVS, JES2 OR SUBSYSTEM  COMMANDS  TO  REMOTE  SYSTEMS,
                RETRIEVE THE RESPONSES. THIS FACILITY MAKES IT POSSIBLE
                AN OPERATOR TO CONTROL (OR AT LEAST MONITOR) MANY MVS HO
                FROM ONE NCCF CONSOLE.














