          RELIABILITY, AVAILABILITY AND SERVICEABILITY

          THE FOLLOWING ENHANCEMENTS HAVE BEEN MADE TO TSSO TO ENHANCE I
          RELIABILITY, AVAILABILITY AND SERVICEABILITY (RAS).

            1.  TSSO NO LONGER ALLOWS THE OPERATOR TO START TSSO IF  IT
                ALREADY  UP. PREVIOUS RELEASES OF TSSO WOULD ALLOW NUMER
                "INCARNATIONS" OF TSSO  ADDRESS  SPACES  TO  EXIST  IN
                SYSTEM.

            2.  SINCE IT MAY OCCASIONALLY BECOME NECESSARY TO  FORCE  ST
                TSSO  (E.G.   DEFEAT THE ABOVE FEATURE), A NEW PARAMETER
                AVAILABLE IN THE PARM FIELD OF THE START  COMMAND  USED
                START  TSSO.  IF  THE  PARAMETER BEGINS WITH A SLASH ('/
                TSSO WILL RESTART OVER ITSELF.

            3.  TSSO ALLOWS AN OPERATOR TO SPECIFY INITIALIZATION  "PROM
                MODE  AS AN OPERAND ON THE START COMMAND. TSSO WILL GO I
                "PROMPT" MODE IF AN "*" IS DETECTED  IMMEDIATELY  PRIOR
                THE  PARMLIB MEMBER SPECIFICATION ON THE START COMMAND.
                EXAMPLE, THE COMMAND

                   S TSSO,PARM='*TSSODECK'


                WILL     START     TSSO     USING      PARAMETERS      F
                'SYS1.PARMLIB(TSSODECK)',  AND  PLACE TSSO IN "PROMPT" M
                FOLLOWING THE READING OF THE PARAMETER INPUT. THE COMMAN


                  S TSSO,PARM='*'


                WILL FORCE TSSO INTO PROMPT MODE AFTER  READING  PARAMET
                FROM THE DEFAULT INITIALIZATION DECK (TSSOPARM).  NOTE T
                IF BOTH NEW OPERANDS (PROMPT  MODE  AND  FORCE  START)
                REQUIRED,  THE '/' MUST BE SPECIFIED FIRST, FOLLOWED BY
                '*', FOLLOWED  BY  THE  NAME  OF  THE  SYS1.PARMLIB  MEM











